name=Advanced Charging Controller (ACC)
version=v2025.5.18-stable.6
versionCode=202505211
author=VR25 (community stable)
description=[community STABLE.6 -- `acca --state` state export, fixed to report the real acc version + a derived charging status + an always-fresh snapshot (rc1 showed empty version, unknown status, and a frozen timestamp). Additive; no charging-behavior change. Includes all STABLE.5 fixes: restored default max_temp to 50C -- stable.4's "gentler 45C" collapsed cooldown_temp and max_temp onto the same value (45 45), which disables the cooldown cycle (it breaks the instant it would start). The sane band is cooldown 45 < max 50 (resume 40, shutdown 55); existing 45/45 configs auto-repair once, no command. ACC is fully STANDALONE (uninstalling the AccA app never removes it -- it is a normal module with its own persistent config); AccA boot receiver registered. Charges to your limit, stops, resumes at your resume level -- a tight cycle in your range. Existing configs auto-migrate, no command. on Pixel/Tensor, no overshoot (driven by the target level on both sides, never "charge to 100 then interrupt"); default discharges down to the limit then HOLDS there (battery-idle), or cycles to the lower limit when idle is off; allow_idle_above_pcap defaults false (never sit above the limit); settings apply within ~1s; daemon survives front-end restarts; fail-safe on every capacity/temp limit + breach watchdog; scanner can LOCK a chosen method. fix9: full fail-safe coverage + flat-hold on all charge-limit nodes + breach watchdog. fix8: malformed-config fail-safe + locked-switch recovery. fix7: Pixel/Tensor cap now HOLDS at the limit. Drives the google charge_stop_level node to pause_capacity so the firmware holds the battery flat at the cap (tight, no overshoot, true idle) instead of toggling 100/5 and sawtoothing past it; switch scanner prefers idle/flat-hold switches; restores retry-on-stall (no daemon re-init mid-pause). Includes fix2-fix6.] Extend your battery's service life by controlling charging current, temperature, and voltage. Any root solution is supported. The installation is always "systemless". Works on Android and KaiOS.
updateJson=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VR-25/acc/master/module.json
